<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus Questions Effectiveness of Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1102094294 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 0600 
GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1102094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus has questioned the 
effectiveness of possible air strikes against Bosnia. Speaking 
at a news conference of the Civic Democratic Party yesterday, he 
emphasized once again that this civil war should be solved not 
by external interference but by internal settlement. Klaus was 
skeptical in particular about air force deployment. He felt 
that, in humane terms, this is unfair. Given this type of civil 
war, in which there are no fronts or clearly defined positions 
of the armies, any global solutions, and air strikes, in 
particular, pose a threat of far greater massacres and 
catastrophes, he asserted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

