<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliamentary Committee Cancels Libya Trip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1102181094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 
GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1102181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jiri Payne, chairman of the Foreign Committee of the 
Chamber of Deputies of the Czech parliament, has canceled his 
trip to Libya. Our parliamentary correspondent Milan Repka 
reports. 
  [Repka] Jiri Payne should have left for a two-day official 
visit to Libya today. According to our information, he decided 
not to go. Deputy Chairman Jan Kasal told Czech radio that the 
Chamber's leadership did not cancel any foreign trips. 
  Pavel Seifer, deputy from the Liberal Social Union, said 
that, in his view, this indicates the Civic Democratic Party's 
[ODS] preparation to quietly dismiss Payne from the post of the 
chairman of the Chamber's Foreign Committee. But ODS press 
spokeswoman Jana Petrova denied this. She told Czech radio that 
the ODS leadership proposed nothing of the kind to Payne. 
  Regarding the connection between Payne's pronouncements 
during his visit to the United States and the abolition of his 
trip to Libya, Petrova said that she did not know why Payne was 
not going to Libya. 
  A meeting of the Chamber of Deputies is due to open on 15 
February. It is likely that a proposal to dismiss the present 
chairman of the foreign committee from his post will be 
submitted there. 

</TEXT>

