<F P=100> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berisha Hails NATO Deadline, Offers Facilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1102214994 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1102214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The president of the republic's spokesman reports 
that President of the Republic Sali Berisha hailed NATO's 
ultimate decision to undertake air strikes if the 10-day 
deadline to withdraw heavy weapons from around Sarajevo is not 
respected or if further bombardments of this city take place, 
with the conviction that this decision will contribute to 
accelerating the establishment of peace in the Republic of 
Bosnia. Berisha also stressed that Albania reconfirms its offer 
of airport facilities that NATO may need to accomplish its 
missions within the UN framework. 
  He also considered the U.S. Administration's decision to 
recognize the Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia as important 
for stability in the region and stressed that the resolution of 
the contradictions between our two neighbors, Greece and 
Macedonia, regarding the name and symbols, is in the interests 
not only of the bilateral relations of these countries but also 
of stability in the south of the Balkans. 

</TEXT>

