<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Asked To Maintain Nonintervention Stance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1002170494 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1002170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nikolay Slatinski, chairman of the Parliamentary 
National Security Commission, today sent a letter to President 
Zhelev in which he states that during the past few days 
increasingly militarist statements are being made and decisions 
adopted in connection with the war in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Bulgaria advocates seeking a peaceful solution to the crisis 
and has repeatedly declared its firm resolve not to intervene in 
any form in the events taking place in former Yugoslavia. At 
this critical juncture, any change in the Bulgarian position is 
absolutely impossible, Slatinski emphasizes in his letter. 
  Nikolay Slatinski appeals to the president to employ his 
constitutional powers more resolutely with a view to achieving 
greater coordination and integration of the efforts of the 
political elite in the legislative and executive powers to 
defend the national position on the crisis in former Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

