<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Boross Cited on Use of Airspace for B-H Raids </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1102173594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1700 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1102173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] NATO aircraft cannot use Hungary's airspace in case 
of an aerial bombing attack against Serbs, the BBC quotes Prime 
Minister Peter Boross. According to the Budapest 
corrrespondent, the Hungarian Government is concerned that by 
allowing NATO to use Hungarian airspace for bombing attacks, 
Hungary would become involved in the war in Yugoslavia, and that 
the step would also harm the situation of Hungarians in 
Vojvodina. 

</TEXT>

