<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albanian Party Supports Air Strike Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1102124394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1149 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1102124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Pristina, 11 Feb (TANJUG) -- The Democratic 
Alliance of Kosovo [DSK] supports the NATO decision to bomb 
Bosnian Serb positions around Sarajevo, DSK deputy president 
Fehmi Agani said at a news conference today. 
  Agani said the lifting of the siege of Sarajevo would put 
both warring sides into an approximately equal position, and 
explained that "as long as the Serbs are holding dominant 
positions there is no basis for a just peaceful solution." 
  Commenting on Albania's official offer of its airports for 
NATO actions in Bosnia, Agani said briefly that "this is 
Albania's obligation, as a member of the international 
community," adding that similar offers had been made by Italy, 
Turkey, and Germany. 
  Agani described DSK president Ibrahim Rugova's visit to the 
United States as successful, in particular the contacts he had 
with President Bill Clinton and representatives of the U.S. 
Administration. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

