<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parties Support Proposal for Early Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502110894 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 0600 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 0600 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Peter Weiss, first deputy chairman of the Slovak 
National Council, has presented to Ivan Gasparovic, chairman of 
the parliament, the official draft of the constitutional law on 
shortening the term of the Slovak parliament. The proposal says 
that, in keeping with the law on local elections, the elections 
should be held on 10-11 November. 
  Vladimir Meciar and Jozef Pokorny, chairmen of the Movement 
for a Democratic Slovakia and the Green Party in Slovakia, spoke 
in favor of shortening the term of the parliament and calling 
early elections. 
  Leaders of the Party of the Democratic Left, the Hungarian 
Christian Democratic Movement, and Coexistence regard early 
elections as the best solution. At their meeting yesterday, they 
agreed that these elections should be held on the same date as 
local elections. 
  The executive committee of the Conservative Democratic 
Party-Democratic Party also supports this alternative. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

