<H3> <TI>   Union Rejects Agreement With Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502105694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 0600 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 0600 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the Kovo trade union, which has 
280,000 trade unionists as members, have decided not to sign 
this year's general agreement with the government. Eugen 
Skultety, deputy chairman of the trade union, said the reason 
for the decision was the government's restrictive measures on 
price regulation due to come into force on 1 April. Citizens 
will not be able to cope with these measures, he said. 

