<H4>   Serbs Threaten Retaliation </H4>
<F P=102> AU1402140894 Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 12 
Feb 94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> AU1402140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The Defense Is Ready"] </F>
  [Text] Major General Zivomir Ninkovic, commander of the 
air force and antiaircraft defense of the Srpska republic army, 
said that there is no real reason, neither political nor 
military, for anyone to directly attack a people. He stressed, 
therefore, that "I do not believe that the NATO threat will be 
realized." 
  In an interview with GLAS SRPSKI, Ninkovic said that if, 
however, the aggression were to take place, "we must not bow, we 
must defend ourselves and succeed at it." 
  Therefore, if the threat is carried out, it will mean that 
we 
have been forced into fighting. In that case, we would use all 
available means for defense, claims General Ninkovic. 

