<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Refuse To Withdraw; Tension Increasing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Krajisnik Rejects NATO Ultimatum </H4>
<F P=102> LD1402153994 Pale Radio-Televizija Republike Srpske Studio-S 
Radio in Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1402153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pale Radio-Televizija Republike Srpske Studio-S 
Radio </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Momcilo Krajisnik, speaker of the Srpska assembly, 
has been speaking at the opening of a sports event on Mt. 
Jahorina, near Sarajevo, to mark 10th anniversary of the 
Sarajevo Olympics: 
  [Begin Krajisnik recording] The international community -- 
the same one that 10 years ago, with its call for peace, 
entrusted to us the holding of the greatest international sports 
competition -- is today calling for bombing and war. It is 
threatening us, without any reason. It is threatening us 
because we are to blame for opposing denigration and 
destruction. We are guilty because we wanted, like all other 
peoples of the former Yugoslavia, to preserve our freedom and 
state. We will reply to their ultimatums in the same way as our 
forebears did. We do not accept the ultimatum. We want freedom 
and peace. We have opted for freedom and are resolved to defend 
the honor of the Serb nation with all available means. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

