<H3> <TI>   Muslim Forces Violate Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502132094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1148 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zvornik, Bratunac, 15 Feb (TANJUG) -- The cease-fire 
agreement for the Sarajevo area has been mainly respected, 
TANJUG learned today from Serb Republic army representatives. 
  According to the same source, the Serb side has been 
directly 
contributing to the implementation of the cease-fire agreement. 
However, the Muslim side has opened infantry fire on the Serb 
side over the last 24 hours from positions in Dobrinja II and 
Dobrinja III and has targeted Serb defense lines on Sanac hill 
and residential areas near the Grbavica stadium. 
  Serb sources cited UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
representatives who had confirmed Muslim building of 
fortifications in the Zuc and Mojmilo areas yesterday. 
  However, the Muslims have resumed reinforcing their 
positions 
in several areas in an attempt to approach Serb positions under 
UNPROFOR protection, Serb military sources warned reporting that 
positions were being reinforced in Dobrinja III, in the area 
between Mojmilo and Sucur Kuce and in the Jewish cemetery. 
  Identical operations to reinforce positions have also been 
registered between Golo Brdo and Ugorsko and between Radovica 
Kuce and Dobrinja Potok, Nedjarici, and Aerodromsko Naselje. 
  The Serb side has informed the UNPROFOR command about this 
and the UNPROFOR command's representatives already stated that 
the building of trenches represented a cease-fire violation. 

</TEXT>

