<H3> <TI>   Serbs Introduce Helicopters on Bihac Assault </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1402151494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1402151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Excerpt] Early this morning, the criminal Mladic brought 
to the Bihac front units from (?Glamoc) which, supported by 
tanks, attacked our positions on the Grmusko-Srbljanski plateau, 
Hasin Vrh, and the Bihac part of the front. 
  In addition to fierce tank and infantry attacks, the 
chetniks 
for the first time used helicopters on the Grmusko-Srbljanski 
plateau. Our soldiers are repelling all attacks, at the same 
time inflicting losses in manpower on the chetniks and letting 
them know that they will never subdue these areas. 
  While the members of the 5th Corps bleed for the ninth 
consecutive day as they struggle against the combined enemy of 
the Muslim people -- the Serbo-Montenegrin aggressor -- the 
members of the paramilitary forces of the so-called autonomous 
province of western Bosnia have attacked -- in a cowardly and 
devious manner -- the members of the [Bosnia-Herzegovina] Army 
in the region of (?Dodig) [words indistinct]. One of our 
soldiers was wounded, while three were tied up and taken to 
Velika Kladusa. This act has elicited more bitterness among the 
members of the 5th Corps and the local population, who say that 
they would all rather die than allow the implementation of the 
autonomists' or the chetniks' plans. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

