<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Affairs Minister Receives NATO Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502115194 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1022 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1502115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 15 Feb--Minister of Foreign Affairs Andrzej 
Olechowski received Field Marshal Richard Vincent, chairman of 
the NATO Military Committee, on Tuesday morning. 
  Andrzej Towpik, director of the MSZ [Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs] department for European institutions, told journalists 
after the meeting had ended that the conversation confirmed the 
openness of the NATO military personnel to both political and 
military cooperation with Poland. Towpik added that the 
conversation was devoted primarily to the Partnership for Peace 
concept. The status of the Polish presentation document, which 
is to be submitted before Poland joins the Partnership for Peace 
programme, was discussed. 
  Towpik emphasized that the partnership concept is a very 
broad program that requires constant discussion. In his opinion 
the Polish side is trying to understand the idea of partnership, 
and NATO representatives will learn in the course of this 
discussion that certain elements of the [Partnership for Peace] 
concept require more precise definition and explanation. 

</TEXT>

