<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Memorandum Rules Out Role in NATO Action </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1402204594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
2000 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1402204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On no account will Hungary participate in a possible 
NATO military action on the territory of the former Yugoslavia. 
This is contained in the memorandum that was handed over today 
in Belgrade by a Hungarian Embassy official. 
  Andras Vince also said that U.S. AWACS reconnaissance planes 
could not stay in Hungarian airspace in the case of a possible 
air strike. The embassy official said that Hungary's Embassy in 
Belgrade was not going to be evacuated for the time being. 
Belgrade radio and television have also reported the Hungarian 
Government's position. 

</TEXT>

