<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatia's Tudjman Visits, Meets With Iliescu </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1402215294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1402215294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The first round of official talks between the 
presidential delegations from Croatia and Romania led by 
Presidents Franjo Tudjman and Ion Iliescu took place at the 
Cotroceni Palace this afternoon. The major part of the 
discussions was devoted to an exchange of opinions about the 
current situation in former Yugoslavia and to ways and means to 
overcome the Bosnian crisis, bearing in mind the recent NATO 
decision and ways to encourage the achievement of a peace 
accord, which is the priority at this stage, Presidency 
Spokesman Ambassador Traian Chebeleu told the media. 
  In this context, President Ion Iliescu greeted the first 
step 
toward the normalization of relations between Serbia and Croatia 
as an important element in seeking a peaceful solution on the 
territory of former Yugoslavia and expressed his readiness to 
support the peace process in general, both within the Geneva 
conference and through bilateral contacts with the other states 
created on the territory of former Yugoslavia. 
  During the talks, the two sides also discussed bilateral 
relations and the determination of the two states to develop 
them. The exchange of opinion between the two presidents will 
also continue during the official dinner that President Ion 
Iliescu is to give in honor of the Croatian President Franjo 
Tudjman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

