<H3> <TI>   Government Not To Evacuate Belgrade Embassy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1402212894 Warsaw TVP Television Second Program Network in 
Polish 2000 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1402212894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TVP Television Second Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Relayed by Warsaw TV Polonia Network] </F>
  [Text] [Announcer] Poland has no intention of withdrawing 
its diplomats from Belgrade, [Foreign Affairs] Minister Andrzej 
Olechowski said after his meeting with Lojze Peterle, the deputy 
prime minister and foreign affairs minister of Slovenia. The 
conflict in former Yugoslavia was also the main subject of 
conversation between the Slovenian foreign minister and 
President Lech Walesa. 
  [Jerzy Chmielewski, ambassador of the Polish Republic to 
Yugoslavia, identified by caption] The charge d'affaires is at 
the embassy at the moment. There are also several Polish 
diplomats there. Several diplomats are working in the trade 
counsellor's office. We also have several delegates of Polish 
trade missions there, as well as the LOT [Polish Airlines] 
office. We are in permanent contact with them, and we will 
react according to the situation. At the moment, we cannot see 
any direct threat to our diplomats. 

