<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Maltese President Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Arbnori Discusses Foreign Policy </H4>
<F P=102> AU0802175194 Tirana ATA in English 0907 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0802175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 8 (ATA) -- "Albania is for good 
relations with all democratic countries without prejudices they 
are small or big ones," Pjeter Arbnori, speaker of the Albanian 
parliament, said today in a meeting with the Malta President Mr. 
Censu Tabone. 
  Speaking about the Albanian foreign policy, Mr. Arbnori said 
"Albania is committed to have good relations with its 
neighbouring countries like Italy, Turkey, Greece, Bulgaria, 
Slovenia, Romania, Croatia, and Macedonia. But we do not have 
good relations with Serbia because it is pursuing a genocidal, 
dictatorial and chauvinistic policy. 
  Concerning the Kosova question, Mr. Arbnori said that 
Albania 
is not for changing the borders by force, but we always will 
defend the rights of the Albanians who live there according to 
all the international charters. 
  "The changes brought about by the reform and the new 
improved 
law on foreign investments are a guarantee for all the foreign 
investors," speaker Arbnori pointed out. 
  President Tabone hailed the Albanian parliament for the work 
it has done in reforming the laws and establishing the 
democratic institutions which will advance Albania toward 
Europe. Considering the parliament as a living reflection of 
the democracy, Mr. Tabone expressed his pleasure for an 
interparliamentary cooperation between Albania and Malta. 
  The Maltese President Tabone said the Albanian approach 
toward Kosova question is very wise and that her right request 
can be solved in the context of the European Union. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

