<H3> <TI>   President's Office: No Comment on Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902172594 Prague CTK in English 1419 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0902172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 9 (CTK) -- Czech President's Office 
will not comment on statements by the chairman of Russia's 
Liberal Democratic Party, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, attacking Czech 
President Vaclav Havel, Halka Hritzova, the office spokeswoman, 
told CTK today. 
  On Tuesday [8 February], Zhirinovskiy told Czech Television: 
"If Vaclav Havel is not pleased by my possible visit (of the 
Czech Republic), then I'm also not pleased that a playwright can 
become a president. It's not right." Zhirinovskiy said this 
after he had confirmed that he had received an invitation to 
visit the Czech Republic from the Assembly for the 
Republic-Czechoslovak Republican Party (SPR-RSC). 
  Zhirinovskiy also predicted that in ten years there would be 
no more Moravia or Sudetenland. "In ten years the entire Czech 
nation will be cursing Havel, just like the Russian people are 
cursing Gorbachev," he said. "Vaclav Havel will die and in ten 
years young Czechs will be cursing him. (Because the Germans) 
will force them to speak German, they will force them to forget 
their mother tongue, they will force them to go to German 
churches and clean the boots of German officers." 
  In his regular Sunday radio speech, Havel said: "Mr. 
Zhirinovskiy holds a diplomatic passport and he therefore can 
come to the Czech Republic anyway. Then it will be up to him 
what he will say here and whether or not our authorities will 
consider it appropriate to expel him eventually. 

</TEXT>

