<H3> <TI>   Serbs Receiving More Aid Than Ethnic Albanians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1002204594 Tirana ATA in English 1111 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1002204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 10 (ATA) -- From the humanitarian 
aid delivered recently in Kosova, 174 tons of food were given to 
the Serbians while 64 tons to the Albanians, RILINDJA of Kosova 
writes on February 9. 
  RILINDJA comments that this proportion is three to one in 
favour of the Serbians when the Albanian population makes up 90 
percent of the whole population in Kosova. 
  At the end of the last year, the surgery clinics received a 
financial aid at a level of 48 thousand USA dollars and an aid 
in medicaments of 7 thousand DM [German marks], but the Albanian 
patients mostly buy their medicaments and other necessary 
materials for the surgeries. 

</TEXT>

