<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 13 February (MTI) -- The Hungarian 
diplomats accredited to Yugoslavia and their families will 
continue to stay in Belgrade, Hungarian foreign affairs 
spokesman Janos Herman told MTI today. Hungary has not made any 
decision on recalling its diplomatic staff from Belgrade, he 
said. 
  The Hungarian Foreign Ministry has been formally informed 
that some diplomatic missions in Belgrade have started 
preparations for evacuation. Since Belgrade cannot be left by 
air, Hungary offers itself as an obvious transit route for the 
departing diplomats. On request, the Foreign Ministry will 
render every possible assistance to them, Herman said. 

