<H3> <TI>   Socialist Party Lists Election Candidates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1402165894 Budapest MTI in English 1817 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1402165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 13 February (MTI) -- In all likelihood, 
Gyula Horn, chairman of the opposition Hungarian Socialist Party 
(MSZP), will head his party's national list in the parliamentary 
elections set for May 8. 
  The second place on the list is occupied by Sandor Nagy, 
president of the National Confederation of Hungarian Trade 
Unions (MSZOSZ), and the third by former finance minister Laszlo 
Bekesi, member of Parliament. 
  The list was compiled at the joint session of the party's 
National Presidium and Board on Saturday [12 February], and will 
be finalized at a party congress on February 27. 
  Horn told reporters that the top places of the list are 
occupied by senior party officials and deputies, who were 
particularly active in the past four years. In a move to open 
towards society, the list includes plenty of non-party people, 
for instance political scientists, artists, and clergymen. 
  Addressing the joint session on Saturday, Sandor Nagy 
announced that the MSZOSZ accepted the MSZP's economic manifesto. 

</TEXT>

