Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 13 February (MTI) -- The parliamentary 
system created over the past four years has become viable so it 
does not need to undergo any sweeping transformation. In the 
future, emphasis should rather be placed on improving its 
operation and increasing its efficiency, the draft electoral 
manifesto of the Hungarian Democratic Forum (MDF) says. 
  The 200-page document, which was distributed among members 
of 
the MDF National Board in Budapest this weekend, will be 
discussed and finalized by the party's three-day national 
congress next weekend. 
  The three chapters of the draft comprise the main issues of 
legislation, home affairs, foreign affairs, economy, 
agriculture, education, culture, health, and social welfare. 

