<H3> <TI>   NATO To Open Information Center for Transylvania </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502122094 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1130 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1502122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES 15/2/1994 -- The Brussels-based 
NATO headquarters has agreed to the setting up in Petrosani an 
information centre of the treaty for the zone of Transylvania, 
central and north-western Romania. For the time being, the 
respective town will host the information office and adequate 
headquarters will be found in future fit for the equipment with 
a computer network to be connected to the NATO centres in 
Europe. A NATO delegation from Brussels is expected to come to 
Petrosani to inspect technical conditions on the spot. 

</TEXT>

