<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: NATO Will Not Extend Deadline </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602143294 Paris AFP in English 1426 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, Feb 16 (AFP) -- The North Atlantic Treaty 
Organisation will not extend its deadline of February 21 for 
besieging Serbs to withdraw their artillery from around Sarajevo 
or face air strikes, a spokesman said Wednesday. 
  He was speaking after a meeting of the ambassadors to NATO 
of 
the 16 member countries, who fixed the deadline on February 9 
after being asked by the United Nations to consider airstrikes 
following the massacre of 68 people by a mortar bomb in a 
Sarajevo market. The Bosnian Serbs have denied firing the bomb 
and a UN commission of inquiry said in Zagreb Wednesday it had 
failed to determine its origin. 
  In Sarajevo the handing over of heavy weapons to UN control 
by both sides, an alternative to their withdrawal, has been 
proceeding at a snail's pace. 

</TEXT>

