<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moldovan Officials Visit To Discuss Trade </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meet With Prime Minister </H4>
<F P=102> AU1502181694 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1600 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1502181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu has received a 
group of dignitaries from the Republic of Moldova led by First 
Deputy Prime Minister Nicolae Andronati at Victoria Palace 
today. The meeting was attended by Romanian Ambassador in 
Chisinau Marian Enache. 
  During the meeting the two sides briefed each other on the 
development of the transition process in the two countries and 
on the specific difficulties of the current period, which are 
being complicated by the energy crisis. The two sides also 
discussed tangible problems pertaining to bilateral relations by 
emphasizing the importance of economic integration both for 
Moldova and Romania. 
  It was stressed that the documents that have been signed and 
those that are to be signed in the coming days will represent 
genuine support for trading companies in the two countries, as 
well as for expanding direct relations between economic units on 
the two banks of the Prut River. 
  Within this context, the two sides noted that relations 
between companies and even between ministries have exceeded 
cooperation at the summit. They agreed that more frequent 
contacts are necessary between the heads of the two governments. 
  Vacaroiu proposed that unsolved problems in economic 
cooperation be checked and examined to identify the best 
solutions swiftly. He assured the high-ranking guests that the 
Romanian Government will continue to support -- economically and 
financially, including through the 1994 budget -- the economy of 
the Republic of Moldova, as well as the economic integration 
process, a press release received from a government spokesman 
points out. 

</TEXT>

