<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This evening President Ion Iliescu received Nicolae 
Andronati, first deputy prime minister of the Republic of 
Moldova, at Cotroceni Palace. The meeting was attended by the 
ministers of economy and trade of the Republic of Moldova, 
Sergiu Certan and Andrei Cheptene, by Marcel Dinu, secretary of 
state at the Romanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and by other 
high-ranking state dignitaries from the two countries. 
  During the meeting President Ion Iliescu was briefed on the 
proceedings of the Intergovernmental Commission. The sides also 
exchanged views on the stage of the national economies of the 
two countries. They also discussed matters pertaining to a more 
profound integration of their economic units, with the sides 
pointing out the increase in the number of joint companies, as 
well as financial-banking issues, Nicolae Andronati told the 
press at the end of the meeting. 

