<H3> <TI>   Responsibility for 5 Feb Attack Undetermined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602124394 Paris AFP in English 1238 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zagreb, Feb 16 (AFP) -- An UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Forces] fact-finding mission has been unable to determine the 
origin of mortar fire that killed 68 people in a Sarajevo market 
earlier this month, an official of the United Nations Protection 
Force in Yugoslavia announced Wednesday. 
  The mortar shell which also wounded 200 other people on 
February 5 may have been fired by either side, Serb or Moslem, 
Canadian Colonel Michel Gauthier, who heads the investigation 
committee, told the press. 

</TEXT>

