<H3> <TI>   Joint Army-Bundeswehr Units To Be Formed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502163294 Prague RUDE PRAVO in Czech 9 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1502163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague RUDE PRAVO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(per)": "There Will Be Joint Exercises and </F>
Also Units With the Bundeswehr"] 
  [Text] Prague--Not only should joint exercises be held in 
the future between the Czech Army and the Bundeswehr, but also 
joint units should be formed within the framework of the 
Partnership for Peace project. This statement was made to 
reporters on Tuesday [8 February] by General J. Nekvasil, chief 
of the Czech Army General Staff. He added that "this will not 
be this year, but next year." 
  The first joint exercises with a Western army will take 
place 
from 15-25 March. Forty Dutch marines will conduct exercises in 
the Czech Republic with the Czech Rapid Deployment Battalion. 
Further joint exercises will be held with the French in the 
May-June period. 

</TEXT>

