<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roman Kovac Expelled From Ruling Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502154094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1500 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Slovak Deputy Prime Minister Roman Kovac and Foreign 
Minister Jozef Moravcik have been expelled from the ruling party 
Movement for a Democratic Slovakia. The Movement's press 
spokewoman Ivana Salczerova confirmed this today. The two 
politicians called last week for forming a new government as a 
broader coalition with the opposition, but without chairmen of 
political parties, including Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar. 

</TEXT>

