<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. F-16 Fighter Plane Crashes; Pilot Safe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602120494 Paris AFP in English 1156 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rome, Feb 16 (AFP) -- A U.S. military fighter plane 
from NATO's base in Aviano, northern Italy, crashed in Slovenia 
Wednesday though the pilot managed to eject from the craft and 
escaped unhurt, informed sources here said. 
  The F-16 crashed while the pilot was attempting to make an 
emergency landing in the former Yugoslav republic bordering 
Italy though it was not immediately known why. 
  Planes at the North Atlantic Treaty Organization base in 
Aviano have been patrolling Bosnian skies for months and are 
among those that would be used should NATO go ahead with its 
threat to launch air strikes on Bosnian Serb forces besieging 
Sarajevo. 

</TEXT>

