<H3> <TI>   Russia's Churkin Departs Zagreb for Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502105794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vitaliy Churkin, special envoy of Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin, departed Zagreb for Sarajevo this morning. He is 
expected to discuss the end of the siege of Sarajevo and its 
demilitarization with Alija Izetbegovic and top officials of the 
Muslim authorities in Bosnia-Herzegovina. Churkin will return 
to Zagreb this afternoon. He is expected to meet officials from 
the Croatian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and to hold a news 
conference. 

