<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Appeals Court Sentences Ex-Politburo Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502214194 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1502214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Tirana Court of Appeal reports 
that an appeal was held in Tirana on 15 February against the 
criminal convictions of defendants Qirjako Mihali, Pali Miska, 
Besnik Bekteshi, Vangjel Cerrava, Prokop Murra, Llambi 
Gegprifti, Muho Artunda, Hajredin Celiku, Foto Cami, and Lenka 
Cuko . 
  As senior political and government leaders at the head of a 
dictatorship, by deliberately abusing their positions the 
defendants granted economic privileges to themselves and their 
families, thus causing serious economic damage to the state and 
the people's interests. 
  For these reasons, under Articles 106 and 31, Paragraphs B 
and D of the Penal Code, the defendants were convicted as 
follows: 
  Qirjako Mihali -- eight years of imprisonment; Pali Miska -- 
six; Besnik Bekteshi -- five; Vangjel Cerrava -- five; Prokop 
Murra -- five; Llambi Gegprifti -- seven; Muho Artunda -- five; 
Hajredin Celiku -- five; Foto Cami -- six; Lenka Cuko -- seven. 
They were also stripped of their decorations and honorary 
titles. 

</TEXT>

