<H3> <TI>   Miners Rally in `Ready To Go' to Bucharest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702122294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1702122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning more than 2,000 miners from the 
Lignite Public Corporation, whose trade unions are affiliated 
with the Lignitul Mining Trade Unions Federation, gathered near 
the aforementioned company headquarters in their working clothes 
ready to go to Bucharest, as was decided last night. Although 
Miron Cosma, leader of the Confederation of Mining Trade Unions 
of Romania, initially fixed a first meeting with the strikers 
for 1200, he arrived there from Petrosani 40 minutes earlier. 
Miron Cosma said that two buses loaded with representatives of 
the miners from pit coal processing centers will come to Targu 
Jiu from the Jiu Valley after 1300 to decide on further joint 
actions. At the same time, he warned that no alcoholic 
beverages should be consumed, but failed to mention the various 
mining tools with which some of the strikers are armed, our 
correspondent Titus Stoichitoiu reports. 

