<H3> <TI>   Trade Union Leader Announces 28 Feb Strike </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602183694 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 14 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1602183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Eugenia Cristea article: "Miron Mitrea Announces That He </F>
Will Organize Such a Strike as Nobody Has Ever Seen Before"] 
  [Text] After the staggering negotiations between political 
parties and trade unions aimed at forming a coalition 
government, in the end Miron Mitrea [chairman of Fratia National 
Confederation of Romania's Free Trade Unions, CNSRL-Fratia] 
stated clearly: "In fact, it is not I whom they had in mind for 
the position of minister of labor, but Victor Ciorbea [chairman 
of the National Confederation of Romania's Free Trade Unions]." 
From Ciorbea, we have learned that he is not willing to accept 
that position either, as long as the government coalition 
includes the Greater Romania Party, Democratic Agrarian Party of 
Romania, National Romanian Unity Party, and Socialist Party of 
Labor. 
  As a result of this, the CNSRL-Fratia, in an almost definite 
cooperation with the Alfa-Trade Union Confederation, takes over 
its duties. 
  "On 28 February we will hold a one-day strike and it will be 
seen not only in the paper or on the television," said Miron 
Mitrea. "Bread factories and bread selling stores alike will 
work only with a third of their capacity, refineries will be 
operating but will not produce anything, oil deliveries will be 
interrupted, drivers will not move from their garages, teachers 
will go to classes but will not teach, and the wood processing 
industry will stop its activity. The telecommunications will be 
interrupted every 10 minutes, road workers will block roads, and 
work will stop at construction sites. Enterprises will have 
strike pickets and nobody from the outside will be allowed to 
enter the factory. The idea is to prove our organizational 
capability and, at the same time, to prepare the ground for our 
future actions planned for March and April." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

