<H3> <TI>   Serbs Vow To Defend Themselves </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20377A Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 31 Jan 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20377A </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by R.M.: "We Will Defend Ourselves"] </F>
  [Text] "If air strikes should be launched against Serbian 
positions in the former Bosnia-Herzegovina, the Serbs will have 
no choice but to defend themselves. We realize that a NATO 
attack on our positions would be an attack by a stronger party 
on a much weaker one, but the Serbs have no right to capitulate." 
  This statement was made yesterday for Radio Kragujevac by 
Momcilo Krajisnik, president of the assembly of the republic of 
Srpska. "Although the Muslims, who rejected the peace plan, are 
responsible for the continuation of the war, the Serbs are being 
threatened." The only reason for this is that the political 
forces that support the Muslims are using the United Nations to 
conduct their politics financed by Islamic countries. 
  On the subject of the continuation of the peace talks in 
Geneva, Krajisnik pointed out that it is very difficult to 
conduct negotiations under the conditions of threats and 
blackmail. Peace should be established as soon as possible; 
weapons should be laid down, and all controversial issues should 
then be calmly resolved through political negotiations. 

</TEXT>

