<H3> <TI>   German Aid Worker Kidnapped </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1702141194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1310 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1702141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cologne (DDP/ADN) -- A worker for the German aid 
organization Cap Anamur was kidnapped by Bosnian Serbs 
yesterday. The chairman of the organization, Rupert Neudeck, 
said on Deutschlandfunk Radio today that the man in question is 
a 32-year-old born in Sarajevo who has held German citizenship 
for a number of years. According to this information he was 
returning to the Dalmatian coast after carrying out relief work 
in Tuzla when the Bosnian Serbs kidnapped him from a bus 
carrying Norwegian doctors. According to available information 
the man is in good shape. 
  The German Government is making efforts through diplomatic 
channels to achieve his release. 
  Neudeck expressed the hope that the work of the aid 
organizations in Bosnia-Herzegovina could continue despite the 
NATO ultimatum to the Serbs. [passage omitted] 

