Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Ratkuzic and Faruk Hajtac from Mostar] </F>
  [Text] Unfavorable weather conditions for carrying out 
combat operations and the significantly more energetic approach 
by the world factors, have obviously (?influenced) the behavior 
of the aggressor's military forces in Bosnia. Sporadic, or 
rather rare small arms provocations and a few mortar shells 
directed at the demarcation lines represent the main 
characteristics of the aggressor's activity in the operational 
zone controlled by the 4th Corps units in the past 24 hours. 
  However, no one seriously believes in the swift and 
permanent 
return of peace to these areas. Namely, despite the cease-fire 
and negotiations between the two sides in Medjugorje, the 
Ustashas yesterday continued carrying out their policy of ethnic 
cleansing by expelling another 10 civilians to the left bank [of 
the Neretva River]. Therefore, it is obvious that the Croatian 
side has not given up its infernal plans and the intention of 
making the area Croatian. 
  This has been Enes Ratukuzic and Faruk Hajtac reporting for 
Radio Television Bosnia-Herzegovina from the 4th Corps 
Information Service. 

