<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Bank Official: Slovakia Repaid Debt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602135394 Prague LIDOVE NOVINY in Czech 9 Feb 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague LIDOVE NOVINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [CTK report: "Slovakia Has Paid $51 Million to the Czech </F>
Republic"] 
  [Text] Prague--The Slovak National Bank yesterday paid $51 
million--that is, 46 million ECU's--to the Czech National Bank 
(CNB). This is the amount by which at the end of January 
Slovakia exceeded its credit margin in the mutual trade clearing 
account. This statement was made on Nova Television by O. 
Kvacek, from the CNB Press Department. CNB press spokesman 
Martin Svehla, in response to a query from CTK, was unable to 
confirm this information. "There is still an imbalance in trade 
between the Czech Republic and Slovakia. The fact is that the 
clearing account balance with Slovakia has already exceeded 6 
billion korunas and that credit has been de facto granted by the 
Czech Republic at this level," said Ota Kaftan, a member of the 
CNB Banking Council. The credit margin was first exceeded at 
the end of last December. The Slovak National Bank settled the 
$43-million deficit ahead of time on 10 January. At that time, 
press spokesman Svehla described this step as highly 
professional. He emphasized that the debt payment took place 
without problems, in time, and precisely in accordance with the 
payments agreement. 

</TEXT>

